two continuations.} (15. Re1 Ra7 $11 {[%cal Ga7f7] Raf7 next and no problems.}) (15. Ng5 $2 {looks serious, but it's a mistake.} e5 $1 16. Nxh7 e4 $1 17. Qh5 Ne5 18. Be2 g6 $1 19. Nxf6+ Qxf6 20. Qg5 {Bacrot-Tari, 2023.} Qe6 $1 $36 {very dangerous for White.}) 15... Nh8 $5 {[%cal Gh8f7] positional, Nf7 next.} (15... e5 {concrete option.} 16. hxg6 e4 17. Bxe4 dxe4 18. Qxe4 (18. gxh7+ Kh8 19. Qxe4 Re8 $1 20. Qxc6 Bg4 $44 {Four pawns down, but it's full compensation :) .}) 18... Re8 19. Qxc6 Be6 $1 20. gxh7+ Kh8 $44 {Same situation: four pawns down but full compensation!}) 16. Bf4 $146 {best and most logical move.} (16. c4 Nf7 $36) (16. Ne5 $2 Bxe5 17. Qxe5 Nf7 18. Qc3 e5 $15 {Karjakin-Asadli.}) 16... Nf7 17. Ne5 Bxe5 18. Bxe5 Qg5 19. Rfe1 a4 $11 {[%csl Ga4] useful move. This is just equal.}) (10. Re1 Ba6 11. c4 (11. Bxa6 Rxa6 12. c4 Nf5 $11 {Lagno-Dreev, 2024.}) 11... Ng6 12. Qc2 Bc5 $1 13. Bxg6 {engine's move, but it cannot be dangerous.} (13. cxd5 Bxd3 14. Qxc5 Qxd5 $11 {is just equal.}) 13... hxg6 14. Nf3 Qb6 $11 {just normal playable position.}) 10... Ba6 {It's very important for us to exchange the bishops.} (10... Ng6 {possible, but not the best.} 11. Re1 Ba6 {And after} 12. Bxg6 hxg6 13. Bg5 Qc7 14. Qd2 $14 {[%csl Ra6,Re8] The bishop on a6 is not so useful, and also the king may be vulnerable. Some questions could be.}) (10... c5 $6 {is met with} 11. c4 $14 {Slightly better for White.}) 11. Bxa6 {The most common move.} (11. Bd2 $5 {Paravyan played this against Bluebaum at the World Cup in 2023. Deep move.} c5 {Also possible, for more complicated game.} (11... Ng6 {Bluebaum played the more positional move.} 12. Qe2 {was tried by Paravyan.} (12. g3 $5 $146 Be7 13. h4 h5 $132 {Just playable position, so 11.Bd2!? is an okay move just to get a game.}) 12... Bxd3 13. cxd3 Be7 $146 {Bluebaum's 13. ..c5 is also possible.} 14. g3 c5 15. h4 Nf8 $11 {[%cal Gf8d7] Just go to d7, support pawn, normal position.}) 12. c4 Nc6 13. Qa4 {looks dangerous for Black, but we can play} Qc7 14. Rfc1 {And now} (14. Bxa5 $4 {fails to} Bxc4 $1 $17 {[%cal Ra5c7,Ga8a4] And big advantage for us.}) 14... d4 {to close the position, and Black's position is okay.} 15. Re1 Bb7 16. h4 Qd7 {[%cal Gc6e5] Nxe5 is a threat.} 17. Qd1 f6 $1 $132 {Very complicated position, difficult to say what's that.}) (11. Re1 {was how Sjugirov played against me, it's just a move.} Bxd3 12. Qxd3 Nf5 $36 {Maybe my position is already better, so Re1 is nothing.}) 11... Rxa6 12. c4 {A lot of strong players went for this position.} (12. Qe2 Ra8 (12... Qa8 $5 $146 {deserves attention.} 13. c4 c5 14. cxd5 Nxd5 $11 {[%cal Gf8e7,Ge8g8] just Be7-00 next.}) 13. c4 Nf5 $1 {[%csl Gf5]} 14. cxd5 cxd5 15. g4 Ne7 $36 {[%cal Gh7h5] h5 next, with a very nice counterplay.}) 12... Ng6 {The best option.} (12... dxc4 $6 {is also not so good.} 13. Bd2 Nd5 14. Qe2 $14 {could be slightly better for White.}) (12... Nf5 $6 {is very risky after} 13. cxd5 cxd5 14. g4 $1 $36 {We have to go back to e7, but no development then.}) 13. Qe2 {White's most common continuation.} (13. cxd5 {premature capture, now we are very comfortable.} cxd5 14. h4 (14. Qe2 {was tried in Valenzuela-Amar, 2023, but after} Ra8 15. g3 Be7 16. h4 h5 $1 {It looks that it may be risky, that h5 could be hanging, but not so easy to target it.} 17. Be3 O-O {[%csl Re5][%cal Rf3g5,Gg6e5] The e5 pawn is also a weakness.} 18. Bd4 Qc8 $1 {[%cal Gc8c4] we are ready for Qc4.} 19. Nh2 (19. Rac1 Qa6 $11) 19... Qc4 $1 20. Qxc4 dxc4 $11 {equal endgame.}) 14... h5 $1 {important, otherwise White plays h4-h5 and we are worse.} 15. Be3 Be7 16. g3 O-O $11 {[%cal Gd8b8,Gf8c8,Ga6c6] we just place the rooks on the 'c' file.}) 13... Ra8 {everybody plays 13...d4, which is good, but it's not necessary to sacrifice a pawn.} (13... d4 {is also good.} 14. Bg5 {The most forced and critical line.} (14. g3 $146 c5 15. h4 h5 $11 {Black is normal, no problem here.} ({or} 15... f5 $5 16. exf6 gxf6 17. h5 Ne7 $13 {also interesting.})) 14... Be7 15. Bxe7 Nxe7 {[%cal Gc6c5] we want to play c5, so the only critical move is} 16. c5 {[%csl Rd4] White will spend time to win the d4 pawn, but we will have compensation.} Ra7 $1 {[%cal Ga7d7]} 17. Rfd1 Rd7 {White can win the pawn in many ways, for example:} 18. Qe4 O-O {[%cal Rf3d4,Ge7f5] Nxd4 impossible because Nf5.} 19. Rxd4 Rxd4 20. Nxd4 Qb8 $1 {[%cal Rb2b3,Gb8b4]} 21. Nb3 Qb5 $11 {[%cal Ge7d5,Gf8b8,Ga5a4] Full compensation. Nd5 or Rb8 or a4 next.}) 14. g3 (14. cxd5 cxd5 15. h4 h5 $1 {transposes in 13.cxd5.}) 14... Be7 15. h4 h5 {[%csl Gc4,Gc6] It is an improved version for White, compared to 13.cxd5, but it is also okay for Black.} 16. Be3 $5 $146 {Engine's recommendation.} (16. Bg5 $146 Qb8 $5 {[%csl Re5][%cal Gb8e5,Re7g5] is an interesting move. The idea is taking on g5, when Ng5 is not possible.} 17. Rfe1 {Logical, but now we can still take it.} Bxg5 18. Nxg5 Ne7 $11 {[%cal Gg7g6,Ge7f5,Ge8f8,Gf8g7] Just normal position, the king will go to g7 via f8, people who play the French know that this is just good position for Black.}) (16. Rd1 Qb8 {[%csl Gb8] very good place for the queen.} 17. Kg2 O-O $11 {[%csl Re5,Rh5] not easy to exploit the h5 pawn because also e5 is weak.}) 16... O-O 17. Rfd1 Qb8 {[%csl Gb8] best place for the queen.} 18. Kg2 Rd8 19. Rac1 Qb7 {This line is not forced, just playable.} 20. Bg5 (20. c5 {If White plays for blockade, then} Qa6 {is good to trade queens.} 21. Qc2 Rdb8 $11 {Normal position.}) 20... dxc4 {is possible now.} 21. Bxe7 Nxe7 22. Rxc4 {A sample line, but after} (22. Ng5 g6 23. Rxc4 Nf5 $13 {Unclear position, no need to go deeper, it's enough.}) 22... Rxd1 23. Qxd1 Qxb2 {We can take a pawn.} 24. Ng5 Qxe5 25. Qxh5 {And important defensive resource:} Qd5+ $1 26. Kh2 {But now you can also make a draw after} (26. Re4 e5 $1 $15 {[%csl Gd5,Gf7][%cal Gd5f7] And maybe Black is better, Qh7 is just a check.}) 26... Qxc4 27. Qxf7+ $11 {[%cal Gf7h5,Gh5f7] With perpetual.} *

