{[%evp 0,28,19,38,60,60,55,44,82,57,17,4,6,7,-9,2,14,14,39,42,41,40,56,40,42,64,70,61,59,53,68]} 1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. dxc5 e6 5. c3 {a lot of strong players used this line.} Nd7 $1 {we play in the same spirit of the 5. Bd3 line.} (5... Bxc5 $2 {most natural and common move, but it's a mistake, and White uses the same idea of the 5.Bd3 line.} 6. Qg4 $1 $16 {[%csl Rg7] no good reaction for Black.}) 6. Nf3 Bxc5 $1 {[%csl Bc5] corret recapture.} (6... Nxc5 $6 {[%csl Gf1] this was good when White's bishop was on d3, but not here.} 7. Be2 {White has an extra tempo if compared to the 5.Bd3 Nd7 6.Nf3 Nxc5 7.Be2 line.} Ne7 8. O-O a6 9. Re1 Bd7 10. Bf1 Bb5 11. Bxb5+ axb5 12. Na3 $16 {[%csl Gc3] big difference pawn on c2 or on c3 (no b4 now).}) 7. Nbd2 {only good move for White.} (7. Bd3 $6 {now White is not in time to consolidate:} f6 $1 {[%csl Bf6] important move.} 8. Qe2 (8. Bf4 $2 fxe5 9. Nxe5 (9. Bxe5 $2 {even worse.} Nxe5 10. Nxe5 Qg5 $19) 9... Qf6 $1 $17 {big advantage.}) 8... fxe5 9. Nxe5 Nxe5 10. Qxe5 Nf6 11. Bb5+ Kf7 $36 {[%csl Cf7][%cal Gc5d6,Gd8c7,Gh8f8] Kf7 is good. Just Bd6-Qc7-Rf8 next.}) 7... Qb6 $1 {[%csl Gb6] important move: we don't allow White to develop in the desired way.} ({If we just play a normal move like} 7... Ne7 {White will be better after} 8. Nb3 Bb6 9. Bd3 $14 {[%cal Gc1f4,Gb3d4] Bf4-Nbd4 next.}) 8. Qe2 {only move.} Qa6 {safest continuation.} ({not} 8... Ne7 $4 9. b4 $18 {[%csl Rc5] we lost our bishop.}) (8... a5 $5 {possible alternative if you feel ambitious.} 9. Nb3 Ne7 10. Nxc5 Nxc5 {[%cal Gb6c7,Gc8d7,Yb7b6,Yc8a6] Qc7-Bd7 or b6-Ba6, very playable position.} 11. h4 $146 {probably the best.} (11. Be3 Qc7 12. O-O-O b6 $132 {[%cal Gc8a6] Ba6 next and no problem.}) 11... h6 12. h5 Bd7 13. Be3 Qc7 14. O-O-O b5 15. Kb1 Ne4 $1 $13 {[%cal Gb5b4] also very playable.}) 9. b4 {only critical move.} (9. Qd1 Qb6 $11 {just draw.}) (9. Qxa6 bxa6 $11 {[%csl Ca6,Ca7] our pawns are good, don't worry.}) 9... Qxe2+ 10. Bxe2 Bf8 $5 {[%cal Gg8e7] we keep free the e7 square for our knight.} (10... Bb6 {also possible, but I prefer the bishop on f8. Why? Because it stops c3-c4!}) 11. Bb2 (11. O-O Ne7 12. Re1 a5 $11 {no problem.}) 11... Ne7 12. c4 {Black is fine in many ways.} Ng6 {Alexey's favorite option.} (12... Nb6 13. c5 Na4 14. Bd4 Bd7 $132) (12... dxc4 {Pier's favorite option.} 13. Nxc4 Nd5 14. a3 N7b6 $11) 13. cxd5 exd5 14. a3 a5 $11 {The move you choose on move 12 is not important and depends more on your personal style. What truly matters is that our position is absolutely fine.} *

